      <title rev="FAC 2021-07 September 10, 2021" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">42.709-3</ph> Responsibilities.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2533e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> The
cognizant contracting officer is responsible for—</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2533e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Determining
whether the penalties in <ph rev="FAC 2021-07 September 10, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>
                           <xref href="42.709-2.dita#FAR_42_709_2"
                                 base="FAR_42_709_1"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">42.709-2</xref>(a)<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend newly redesignated section 42.709-3 by—
a. In paragraph (a)(1) removing “42.709-1(a)” and adding “42.709-2(a)” in its place;?></ph> should
be assessed;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2533e28" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Determining
whether such penalties should be waived pursuant to <ph rev="FAC 2021-07 September 10, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>
                           <xref href="42.709-5.dita#FAR_42_709_5"
                                 base="FAR_42_709_5"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">42.709-5</xref>;<?FM MARKER [Why] b. In paragraph (a)(2) removing “42.709-5” and adding “42.709-6” in its place; and?></ph> and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2533e40" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Referring
the matter to the appropriate criminal investigative organization
for review and for appropriate coordination of remedies, if there
is evidence that the contractor knowingly submitted unallowable
costs.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2533e45" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The contract
auditor, in the review and/or the determination of final indirect
cost proposals for contracts subject to this section, is responsible
for—</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2533e51" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Recommending
to the contracting officer which costs may be unallowable and subject
to the penalties in <ph rev="FAC 2021-07 September 10, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>
                           <xref href="42.709-2.dita#FAR_42_709_2"
                                 base="FAR_42_709_1"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">42.709-2</xref>(a)<?FM MARKER [Why] c. In paragraph (b)(1) removing “42.709-1(a)” and adding “42.709-2(a)” in its place.?></ph>;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2533e63" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Providing
rationale and supporting documentation for any recommendation; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2533e68" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Referring
the matter to the appropriate criminal investigative organization
for review and for appropriate coordination of remedies, if there
is evidence that the contractor knowingly submitted unallowable
costs.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
